(16304, 2, '2013-07-16 15:23:24', '2013-07-16 15:23:24', '<a href="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/64-Mercedes-230SL-Main-Photo.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16305" alt="64 Mercedes 230SL Main Photo" src="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/64-Mercedes-230SL-Main-Photo-1024x605.jpg" width="584" height="345" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nTaking place the first weekend of August, we have a very special, early 1964 Mercedes-Benz 230SL being auctioned at the first annual Auctions America California Sale. Throughout the past few years, Auctions America, which is a subsidiary of RM Auctions, has gained recognition and now competes with names like Russo &amp; Steele and Mecum. The star cars of this sale include a great Mercedes 300SL Roadster with a lot of originality points that we love to see, as well as a 72 Ferrari 365 GTC/4 sitting on Borrani wire wheels. In fact, we actually own one of these 365’s that is getting an extensive amount of engine work done which should be available in the coming months.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAuctions America is looking to kick off this new sale with a bang by partnering with NBC Sports Network. NBC will be broadcasting live coverage of the sale and it just so happens that our little 230SL will have its 15 minutes of fame during one of the 3 days.  The car is particularly special because of its stunning original colors of black with red interior. Along with the rare color combination is the list of factory options that include leather interior, Becker radio, side view mirror, and power steering. In celebration of the 50<sup>th</sup> Anniversary of the “Pagoda” Mercedes, LBI wanted to offer at auction, the purest form of Pagoda motoring in rare, desirable colors complete with a recent restoration and 2-tops.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPlease visit the <a href="http://www.auctionsamerica.com/events/overview.cfm?SaleCode=BB13">Auctions America</a> site for more details about the 3 day sale. To view our car, please <a href="http://www.auctionsamerica.com/events/all-lots.cfm?order=runorder&amp;noreserve=&amp;Day=&amp;category=&amp;year=Year+or+Lot+Number&amp;make=Mercedes-Benz&amp;model=Model&amp;SaleCode=BB13">click here</a>. Keep up to date with everything we are doing by following us on <a href="http://instagram.com/luxurybrokersint#">Instagram</a> and<a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Luxury-Brokers-International/165561913469224?ref=hl"> Facebook</a>. Thank you for reading this weeks blog!', 'Our 64 Mercedes 230SL on NBC Sports TV', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'our-64-mercedes-230sl-on-nbc-sports-tv', '', '', '2013-07-16 15:23:24', '2013-07-16 15:23:24', '', 0, 'http://www.lbilimited.com/?p=16304', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(16310, 2, '2013-07-25 15:54:24', '2013-07-25 15:54:24', '<a href="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photo-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16312" alt="photo 2" src="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photo-2-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>\n\nEvery true car guy yearns to discover that old forgotten beauty in the back of a barn or garage covered in decades of dust. On a couple occasions, LBI has had the barn find dream come true.  As many barn finds so often do, our find came out of left field when an unsuspecting gentleman walking down the street mentioned if we wanted to see some old Rolls-Royces. This particular find was located 2 blocks from our newly renovated warehouse! The folks at <a href="www.barnfinds.com/">barnfinds.com</a> took interest in our story and decided to publish it on their website. You may remember, a few blog postings ago, we talked about a dual Jaguar find that was also featured on barnfinds.com and in their yearly calendar: <a href="http://www.barnfinds.com/calendar-car-1963-jaguar-e-type/">http://www.barnfinds.com/calendar-car-1963-jaguar-e-type/</a>\n\nThe Rolls-Royce find was equally as exciting and I urge any of you car enthusiast to read our story below!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>“Some people say barn finds are getting slim, after all automotive archeology is very popular, with more and more people out there hunting, and indeed finding. The most interesting and unusual of finds tend to come when you least expect it. Adolfo Massari and I (Andrew Mastin) were only a few days into relocating Luxury Brokers International to our new facility here in the Frankford section of Philadelphia. As I pulled up to our new shop one morning, I could hardly get out of my truck before an SUV pulled up beside me, put down the window, and asked “hey, do you want to see some old cars”? Having seen our collection migrate, this gentlemen must have taken notice and figured we might like what we were about to see; and was he ever right. We followed him about 2 blocks then stopped in front of a circa 1950’s warehouse, walked in, shook a few hands and were then blown away.</em>\n\n<em>In front of us, stationary for nearly 30+ years was a dusty old 1937 Rolls Royce Wraith Sedanca by Windovers; a reported one of 3 made. It was a very original car throughout, sitting on flat tires, and clearly forgotten. As the story goes, the car was owned by the warehouse owner’s father since the early 1950’s when he purchased it from Inskip in NYC. The car was enjoyed for many years as the father was a RROC club member. Unfortunately he fell ill and the car was put away. Some interesting conversation and a bag of cash later, it ended up as a sight to behold at our new facility. There’s nothing like walking into the shop first thing in the AM and seeing an old relic, still dusty and barn fresh. It reminded us of why we are out there every day doing what we do, because we love cars and the thrill of the find!”</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFor the full write-up and picture set, click on the following link: <a href="http://www.barnfinds.com/warehouse-wraith-1937-rolls-royce/">Warehouse Wraith: 1937 Rolls-Royce</a>. Additionally, take a look at our <a href="http://www.lbilimited.com/manufacturers/current-offerings/">current offerings tab</a> to see what’s new in the LBI stable!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photo-32.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16313" alt="photo 3" src="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/photo-32-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Sitting 30 Years: 37 Rolls-Royce Discovered!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sitting-30-years-37-rolls-royce-discovered', '', '', '2013-07-25 15:54:24', '2013-07-25 15:54:24', '', 0, 'http://www.lbilimited.com/?p=16310', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(16323, 2, '2013-08-12 22:16:08', '2013-08-12 22:16:08', 'Hectic. The only word to describe this time of year as classic car guys. Between local and regional shows, Monterey car week, and daily operations, our schedule is packed! Tomorrow at this time, we will be arriving in San Francisco, CA to begin a grueling but fun week long adventure on the California coast. We are extremely excited to view the record setting auction results that are surely on the horizon. Personally, we think RM Auctions has the best line up this year and arguably the best set of cars for an auction setting. Period. Heavy hitters include the 2012 Pebble Beach Best of Show winning 1928 Mercedes-Benz 680S Torpedo by Saoutchik, a 1939 Mercedes-Benz 540K Special Roadster, and 1955 Jaguar D-Type. One of our favorites is RM\'s 1955 Mercedes-Benz 300SL Gullwing in stunning Graphite Grey over Red leather with original paint, interior, and rudge wheels. For those of you attending the festivities please join us for the following events:\n\n-The Rolex Monterey Historics Racing at Leguna Seca Racway August 16<sup>th</sup>-18<sup>th</sup>\n\n-Legands of the Autobahn Friday August 16<sup>th</sup>\n\n-RM, Gooding, Bonhams, and Russo &amp; Steele Auctions\n\n-Pebble Beach Concours d’Elegance Sunday August 18th\n\n&nbsp;\n\nDuring labor day weekend, we will have two cars going through the Auctions America Fall Auburn Sale. A beautifully restored 1957 Mercedes-Benz 190SL Roadster in blue over parchment interior <a href="http://auctionsamerica.com/events/feature-lots.cfm?SaleCode=AF13&amp;ID=r781&amp;Order=runorder&amp;feature=&amp;collection=&amp;grouping=&amp;category=">seen here</a> as well as an excellent driver quality 1971 Mercedes-Benz 280SL<a href="http://auctionsamerica.com/events/feature-lots.cfm?SaleCode=AF13&amp;ID=r661&amp;Order=runorder&amp;feature=&amp;collection=&amp;grouping=&amp;category="> found here</a>. The sale of this little 280SL will be broadcasted live on NBC Sports TV! Additionally, Worldwide Auctioneers gave our 1966 Porsche 911 SWB a four page spread for their Auburn sale catalog.\n\n<a href="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-16326" alt="photo 1" src="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-1-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a>\n\n<a href="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-16327" alt="photo 2" src="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-2-300x225.jpg" width="300" height="225" /></a>\n\nA few weekends ago, our assistant, Diana helped with a wedding that took place on a beautiful lake setting where our 280SL Mercedes was the token “Just Married” vehicle. Zen Photography snapped some excellent photos that we would like to share below!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Etherington-Libson-Wedding-Reception-0043.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-16324" alt="View More: http://zenphotography.pass.us/libsonwedding" src="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Etherington-Libson-Wedding-Reception-0043-682x1024.jpg" width="584" height="876" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Etherington-Libson-Wedding-Reception-0057.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-16325" alt="View More: http://zenphotography.pass.us/libsonwedding" src="http://www.lbilimited.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Etherington-Libson-Wedding-Reception-0057-1024x682.jpg" width="584" height="388" /></a>', 'Events, Record Setting Weekend, and NBC Sports', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'events-record-setting-weekend-and-nbc-sports', '', '', '2013-08-12 22:16:08', '2013-08-12 22:16:08', '', 0, 'http://www.lbilimited.com/?p=16323', 0, 